com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds

Enum AlarmSeverity

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AlarmSeverity>
      • com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds.AlarmSeverity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<AlarmSeverity>

    @ThreadSafety(level=COMPLETELY_THREADSAFE)
public enum AlarmSeverity
extends java.lang.Enum<AlarmSeverity>
    This class provides information about the types of alarm severities that may be included in alarm entries.
    NOTE: This class, and other classes within the com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds package structure, are only supported for use against Ping Identity, UnboundID, and Alcatel-Lucent 8661 server products. These classes provide support for proprietary functionality or for external specifications that are not considered stable or mature enough to be guaranteed to work in an interoperable way with other types of LDAP servers.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      CRITICAL
      The alarm severity that indicates there is a critical error condition.
      INDETERMINATE
      The alarm severity that indicates that the severity cannot be determined.
      MAJOR
      The alarm severity that indicates there is a major error condition.
      MINOR
      The alarm severity that indicates there is a minor error condition.
      NORMAL
      The alarm severity that indicates that the associated condition is normal.
      WARNING
      The alarm severity that indicates there is a warning condition.
